    <node id="RT-DETR">
      <data key="entity_id">RT-DETR</data>
      <data key="entity_type">method</data>
      <data key="description">A real-time end-to-end object detector that outperforms YOLO detectors and eliminates NMS post-processing.&lt;SEP&gt;RT-DETR is the first real-time end-to-end object detector proposed to address speed and accuracy dilemmas in object detection.&lt;SEP&gt;A real-time object detection model proposed in the paper, designed to improve accuracy and reduce computational redundancy.</data>
      <data key="source_id">chunk-58459ff4307a5aa040657ceba41be948&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf30e7371cd8c7ca86d01ccde3c99b27&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4e9e2c6c4fdb29309e868b2570de1575</data>
      <data key="file_path">23rfewdq.pdf</data>
      <data key="created_at">1773737997</data>
      <data key="truncate" />
    </node>
    <node id="YOLO">
      <data key="entity_id">YOLO</data>
      <data key="entity_type">method</data>
      <data key="description">YOLO is a popular framework for real-time object detection known for its speed and accuracy trade-off but affected by NMS.</data>
      <data key="source_id">chunk-58459ff4307a5aa040657ceba41be948</data>
      <data key="file_path">23rfewdq.pdf</data>
      <data key="created_at">1773737745</data>
      <data key="truncate" />
    </node>
    <node id="DETR">
      <data key="entity_id">DETR</data>
      <data key="entity_type">method</data>
      <data key="description">An end-to-end object detector based on Transformer proposed by Carion et al., eliminating anchor and NMS components.&lt;SEP&gt;DETR refers to end-to-end Transformer-based detectors that eliminate NMS but suffer from high computational costs.&lt;SEP&gt;An end-to-end object detector discussed in the related work section as a foundational model.</data>
      <data key="source_id">chunk-58459ff4307a5aa040657ceba41be948&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf30e7371cd8c7ca86d01ccde3c99b27&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4e9e2c6c4fdb29309e868b2570de1575</data>
      <data key="file_path">23rfewdq.pdf</data>
      <data key="created_at">1773737997</data>
      <data key="truncate" />
    </node>
    <node id="DINO">
      <data key="entity_id">DINO</data>
      <data key="entity_type">method</data>
      <data key="description">DINO is a detector model used for comparison, specifically the DINO-R50 variant which RT-DETR outperforms.&lt;SEP&gt;DINO suggests mixed query selection to help better initialize queries.&lt;SEP&gt;Query initialization method discussed in Section 2.2.&lt;SEP&gt;An object detection model variant discussed in the related work section.</data>
      <data key="source_id">chunk-58459ff4307a5aa040657ceba41be948&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf30e7371cd8c7ca86d01ccde3c99b27&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4e9e2c6c4fdb29309e868b2570de1575&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5f1730cd434432b577c6ebd8443bdc2f</data>
      <data key="file_path">23rfewdq.pdf</data>
      <data key="created_at">1773737997</data>
      <data key="truncate" />
    </node>
    <node id="NMS">
      <data key="entity_id">NMS</data>
      <data key="entity_type">method</data>
      <data key="description">Non-Maximum Suppression is an operation used to filter prediction boxes, sensitive to hyperparameters like confidence and IoU thresholds.&lt;SEP&gt;NMS is a process that negatively affects the speed and accuracy of YOLOs, which DETRs aim to eliminate.&lt;SEP&gt;NMS is a post-processing algorithm used to eliminate overlapping output boxes in object detection.&lt;SEP&gt;Non-Maximum Suppression, a technique analyzed for its impact within the RT-DETR framework.</data>
      <data key="source_id">chunk-58459ff4307a5aa040657ceba41be948&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf30e7371cd8c7ca86d01ccde3c99b27&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf0447c8449e48c02de19b9101a7eb5b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4e9e2c6c4fdb29309e868b2570de1575</data>
      <data key="file_path">23rfewdq.pdf</data>
      <data key="created_at">1773737997</data>
      <data key="truncate" />
    </node>
    <node id="CNN">
      <data key="entity_id">CNN</data>
      <data key="entity_type">method</data>
      <data key="description">CNN is a type of neural network architecture used in YOLOv1 for object detection.&lt;SEP&gt;CNN-based architecture is commonly adopted by existing real-time detectors like YOLO.</data>
      <data key="source_id">chunk-58459ff4307a5aa040657ceba41be948&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf30e7371cd8c7ca86d01ccde3c99b27</data>
      <data key="file_path">23rfewdq.pdf</data>
      <data key="created_at">1773737745</data>
      <data key="truncate" />
    </node>
    <node id="Hybrid Encoder">
      <data key="entity_id">Hybrid Encoder</data>
      <data key="entity_type">method</data>
      <data key="description">Hybrid Encoder is an efficient encoder designed for RT-DETR to process multi-scale features by decoupling interactions.</data>
      <data key="source_id">chunk-58459ff4307a5aa040657ceba41be948</data>
      <data key="file_path">23rfewdq.pdf</data>
      <data key="created_at">1773737745</data>
      <data key="truncate" />
    </node>
    <node id="Uncertainty-Minimal Query Selection">
      <data key="entity_id">Uncertainty-Minimal Query Selection</data>
      <data key="entity_type">method</data>
      <data key="description">Uncertainty-Minimal Query Selection is a method proposed to provide high-quality initial queries to the decoder in RT-DETR.</data>
      <data key="source_id">chunk-58459ff4307a5aa040657ceba41be948</data>
      <data key="file_path">23rfewdq.pdf</data>
      <data key="created_at">1773737745</data>
      <data key="truncate" />
    </node>
    <node id="Real-Time Object Detection">
      <data key="entity_id">Real-Time Object Detection</data>
      <data key="entity_type">concept</data>
      <data key="description">Real-Time Object Detection is the research area focused on detecting objects quickly with applications like autonomous driving.</data>
      <data key="source_id">chunk-58459ff4307a5aa040657ceba41be948</data>
      <data key="file_path">23rfewdq.pdf</data>
      <data key="created_at">1773737745</data>
      <data key="truncate" />
    </node>
    <node id="COCO">
      <data key="entity_id">COCO</data>
      <data key="entity_type">data</data>
      <data key="description">COCO is a dataset used to evaluate the accuracy of RT-DETR, where it achieved 53.1% / 54.3% AP.&lt;SEP&gt;A dataset used to evaluate the performance of the RT-DETR model, specifically for accuracy metrics.</data>
      <data key="source_id">chunk-58459ff4307a5aa040657ceba41be948&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4e9e2c6c4fdb29309e868b2570de1575</data>
      <data key="file_path">23rfewdq.pdf</data>
      <data key="created_at">1773737997</data>
      <data key="truncate" />
    </node>
    <node id="Objects365">
      <data key="entity_id">Objects365</data>
      <data key="entity_type">data</data>
      <data key="description">Objects365 is a dataset used for pre-training RT-DETR to achieve performance improvements.&lt;SEP&gt;Objects365 is a dataset used for pre-training the RT-DETR model to improve accuracy.</data>
      <data key="source_id">chunk-58459ff4307a5aa040657ceba41be948&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf30e7371cd8c7ca86d01ccde3c99b27</data>
      <data key="file_path">23rfewdq.pdf</data>
      <data key="created_at">1773737745</data>
      <data key="truncate" />
    </node>
    <node id="T4 GPU">
      <data key="entity_id">T4 GPU</data>
      <data key="entity_type">artifact</data>
      <data key="description">T4 GPU is hardware used to measure the Frames Per Second of the RT-DETR model.&lt;SEP&gt;T4 GPU is the hardware used to test the speed of the NMS operation with TensorRT FP16.&lt;SEP&gt;Hardware used to measure the inference speed of the RT-DETR model during testing.</data>
      <data key="source_id">chunk-58459ff4307a5aa040657ceba41be948&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf0447c8449e48c02de19b9101a7eb5b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4e9e2c6c4fdb29309e868b2570de1575</data>
      <data key="file_path">23rfewdq.pdf</data>
      <data key="created_at">1773737997</data>
      <data key="truncate" />
    </node>
    <node id="Transformer">
      <data key="entity_id">Transformer</data>
      <data key="entity_type">method</data>
      <data key="description">Transformer is an architecture used in DETR for end-to-end object detection.&lt;SEP&gt;Transformer is the underlying architecture for DETR-based detectors.</data>
      <data key="source_id">chunk-58459ff4307a5aa040657ceba41be948&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf30e7371cd8c7ca86d01ccde3c99b27</data>
      <data key="file_path">23rfewdq.pdf</data>
      <data key="created_at">1773737745</data>
      <data key="truncate" />
    </node>
    <node id="Uncertainty-minimal Query Selection">
      <data key="entity_id">Uncertainty-minimal Query Selection</data>
      <data key="entity_type">method</data>
      <data key="description">Uncertainty-minimal Query Selection is a method proposed to provide high-quality initial queries to the decoder.&lt;SEP&gt;A specific technique discussed in the Introduction for improving model performance.</data>
      <data key="source_id">chunk-58459ff4307a5aa040657ceba41be948&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4e9e2c6c4fdb29309e868b2570de1575</data>
      <data key="file_path">23rfewdq.pdf</data>
      <data key="created_at">1773737997</data>
