    <node id="RT-DETR Paper Page 1 (image)">
      <data key="entity_id">RT-DETR Paper Page 1 (image)</data>
      <data key="entity_type">image</data>
      <data key="description">Page 1 of the RT-DETR research paper manuscript containing the conclusion of the Introduction, a list of main contributions, and the beginning of the Related Work section. The text details RT-DETR performance metrics compared to YOLO and DETR models. The page follows a two-column academic format and ends with a sentence fragment continuing to page 2.</data>
      <data key="source_id">chunk-4e9e2c6c4fdb29309e868b2570de1575</data>
      <data key="file_path">23rfewdq.pdf</data>
      <data key="created_at">1773737834</data>
    </node>
    <node id="RT-DETR Paper Page 2 - NMS Analysis and Speed Benchmark (image)">
      <data key="entity_id">RT-DETR Paper Page 2 - NMS Analysis and Speed Benchmark (image)</data>
      <data key="entity_type">image</data>
      <data key="description">This image represents page two of the RT-DETR research paper, focusing on the limitations of YOLO detectors due to Non-Maximum Suppression (NMS). The page features Figure 2 illustrating box counts at varying confidence thresholds and Table 1 quantifying the trade-off between NMS hyperparameters, accuracy (AP), and execution time. Section 3 establishes an end-to-end speed benchmark to justify the need for RT-DETR. The content bridges related work on DETRs with the empirical analysis motivating the proposed real-time detector.</data>
      <data key="source_id">chunk-5f1730cd434432b577c6ebd8443bdc2f</data>
      <data key="file_path">23rfewdq.pdf</data>
      <data key="created_at">1773737834</data>
    </node>
    <node id="knowledge_vision_pages_page_3 (image)">
      <data key="entity_id">knowledge_vision_pages_page_3 (image)</data>
      <data key="entity_type">image</data>
      <data key="description">This image reference points to page 3 of a vision knowledge documentation collection stored in a local GitHub repository structure. The file path suggests it is part of a structured document system for knowledge retrieval purposes. Actual visual content cannot be determined without image access.</data>
      <data key="source_id">chunk-bd28aa27be2f18b8904be9e646aae317</data>
      <data key="file_path">23rfewdq.pdf</data>
      <data key="created_at">1773737834</data>
    </node>
    <node id="RT-DETR Paper Page 1 (image) [image_asset p0]">
      <data key="entity_type">image_asset</data>
      <data key="description">Page 1 of the RT-DETR research paper manuscript containing the conclusion of the Introduction, a list of main contributions, and the beginning of the Related Work section. The text details RT-DETR performance metrics compared to YOLO and DETR models. The page follows a two-column academic format and ends with a sentence fragment continuing to page 2.</data>
