    <node id="RT-DETR Paper Page 2 - NMS Analysis and Speed Benchmark (image) [image_asset p1]">
      <data key="entity_type">image_asset</data>
      <data key="description">This image represents page two of the RT-DETR research paper, focusing on the limitations of YOLO detectors due to Non-Maximum Suppression (NMS). The page features Figure 2 illustrating box counts at varying confidence thresholds and Table 1 quantifying the trade-off between NMS hyperparameters, accuracy (AP), and execution time. Section 3 establishes an end-to-end speed benchmark to justify the need for RT-DETR. The content bridges related work on DETRs with the empirical analysis motivating the proposed real-time detector.</data>
      <data key="source_id">image_asset:img-11265c48f93da9b69350557d03e3b273</data>
