    <node id="Kongzi Paper Page 1 with Figure 1 (image)">
      <data key="entity_id">Kongzi Paper Page 1 with Figure 1 (image)</data>
      <data key="entity_type">image</data>
      <data key="description">This image is the first page of the research paper introducing 'Kongzi,' a large language model optimized for historical accuracy. It features the abstract and introduction text alongside Figure 1, which illustrates the model's capability to detect and correct factual hallucinations in historical narratives compared to other LLMs. The figure uses a comparative layout to show how misleading prompts can lead to errors and how Kongzi addresses this through structured fact-checking.</data>
      <data key="source_id">chunk-94f9d8d2787b0a25fb70dd046d2d4d9c</data>
      <data key="file_path">3091_Kongzi_A_Historical_Large (5).pdf</data>
      <data key="created_at">1773740202</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Kongzi_Historical_LLM_Methodology_Page (image)">
      <data key="entity_id">Kongzi_Historical_LLM_Methodology_Page (image)</data>
      <data key="entity_type">image</data>
      <data key="description">This image captures a page from the 'Kongzi' research paper, detailing the methodology for creating a historical large language model. It outlines the model's core contributions—continued pre-training, CoT data generation, and fact-aware reinforcement learning—and provides specific technical details on data acquisition, including the processing of 0.2 billion tokens of Chinese historical text. The content bridges the gap between related work in reasoning models and the specific implementation strategies used to enhance factual accuracy in historical domains.</data>
      <data key="source_id">chunk-3422b4a40b3460c1d6373eb28c969bfc</data>
      <data key="file_path">3091_Kongzi_A_Historical_Large (5).pdf</data>
      <data key="created_at">1773740202</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Machine Learning Pipeline Overview and Training Strategy Page (image)">
      <data key="entity_id">Machine Learning Pipeline Overview and Training Strategy Page (image)</data>
      <data key="entity_type">image</data>
      <data key="description">This image presents Figure 2 and accompanying text from a research paper describing a multi-stage machine learning pipeline. The workflow involves data cleaning, augmentation, and Chain-of-Thought (CoT) generation, followed by Continue Pre-Training (CPT), two-stage Supervised Fine-Tuning (SFT), and Content Reinforcement Learning (RL). The text elaborates on data generation strategies, initial training to enhance reasoning capabilities, and a reinforcement learning approach using a Historical Fact-enhanced Reward Module (HFRM) to reduce hallucinations.</data>
      <data key="source_id">chunk-6e2e34ba6d8c314ebbcac375f0cdddb3</data>
      <data key="file_path">3091_Kongzi_A_Historical_Large (5).pdf</data>
      <data key="created_at">1773740202</data>
    </node>
    <node id="HFRM Architecture and GRPO Objective Function Diagram (image)">
      <data key="entity_id">HFRM Architecture and GRPO Objective Function Diagram (image)</data>
      <data key="entity_type">image</data>
      <data key="description">This image presents Figure 3 from a technical paper, illustrating the Historical Fact-enhanced Reward Module (HFRM). The diagram visualizes a pipeline where a Policy Model generates text that is evaluated against Ground Truth using knowledge graph embeddings and cosine similarity. The accompanying text defines the mathematical framework for Generalized Reward Policy Optimization (GRPO), emphasizing the use of semantic similarity as a reward signal to improve factual accuracy in AI models.</data>
      <data key="source_id">chunk-0b3eed9e14ebcd71d26f8def5455cc57</data>
      <data key="file_path">3091_Kongzi_A_Historical_Large (5).pdf</data>
      <data key="created_at">1773740202</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Kongzi Model Performance Chart and Experimental Methodology Page (image)">
      <data key="entity_id">Kongzi Model Performance Chart and Experimental Methodology Page (image)</data>
      <data key="entity_type">image</data>
      <data key="description">This image shows Figure 4 comparing Kongzi model variants against other LLMs under three judge models, alongside detailed experimental methodology including dataset curation, preprocessing, and multi-stage training protocols using classical Chinese historical corpora and GPU infrastructure.</data>
      <data key="source_id">chunk-6e630076ef2df97668feb03cabe4e2fc</data>
      <data key="file_path">3091_Kongzi_A_Historical_Large (5).pdf</data>
      <data key="created_at">1773740202</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Kongzi Model Performance Metrics and RL Framework Documentation (image)">
      <data key="entity_id">Kongzi Model Performance Metrics and RL Framework Documentation (image)</data>
      <data key="entity_type">image</data>
      <data key="description">This image contains a page from a research paper detailing the performance improvements of the 'Kongzi' AI models (0.5B and 7B parameters) achieved through Reinforcement Learning (RL) training. It features a comprehensive data table comparing RL-trained models against SFT baselines across metrics like logical reasoning and problem solving when evaluated against GPT-4o, Gemini-2.5, and Qwen-Max. The text further elaborates on the GRPO reinforcement learning framework, defining specific reward functions for factual accuracy, formatting, and repetition penalties used to optimize the model's output.</data>
      <data key="source_id">chunk-73d927553a48f3efc08f223d626070d0</data>
      <data key="file_path">3091_Kongzi_A_Historical_Large (5).pdf</data>
      <data key="created_at">1773740202</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Kongzi Model Performance Evaluation and Conclusion Page (image)">
      <data key="entity_id">Kongzi Model Performance Evaluation and Conclusion Page (image)</data>
      <data key="entity_type">image</data>
      <data key="description">This image captures page 7 of a research paper introducing 'Kongzi,' a language model designed for historical domains. It features Table 2, presenting benchmark results on CMMLU-Chinese-History comparing Kongzi against models like Qwen and Deepseek. The text details the evaluation methodology involving human and LLM scoring and concludes with a summary of the model's achievements through reinforcement learning and cold-start training, followed by a list of references.</data>
      <data key="source_id">chunk-dc033750199f8c7105725aa466d5fb7a</data>
      <data key="file_path">3091_Kongzi_A_Historical_Large (5).pdf</data>
      <data key="created_at">1773740202</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Academic Bibliography Page on Large Language Models (image)">
      <data key="entity_id">Academic Bibliography Page on Large Language Models (image)</data>
      <data key="entity_type">image</data>
      <data key="description">This image captures page 8 of a research paper's reference list, featuring a dense compilation of citations focused on recent advancements in Large Language Models (LLMs). It includes technical reports and surveys from major AI entities such as OpenAI, DeepSeek, and Qwen, covering topics like reasoning capabilities, hallucination, and preference optimization, with publication dates ranging primarily from 2023 to 2025.</data>
      <data key="source_id">chunk-bc7abdd4fe5086ee405183c79ba25201</data>
      <data key="file_path">3091_Kongzi_A_Historical_Large (5).pdf</data>
      <data key="created_at">1773740202</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Academic Bibliography Page on AI and LLMs (image)">
      <data key="entity_id">Academic Bibliography Page on AI and LLMs (image)</data>
      <data key="entity_type">image</data>
      <data key="description">This image captures a bibliography page listing ten academic references focused on advanced machine learning topics such as Reinforcement Learning from Human Feedback (RLHF), Chain-of-Thought reasoning, and Large Language Model alignment. The citations range from 2017 to 2025 and include sources from NeurIPS conferences and arXiv preprints, indicating a research context involving state-of-the-art AI methodologies.</data>
      <data key="source_id">chunk-39a47cbb95bd0b6829e2c7d96fe0c0a3</data>
      <data key="file_path">3091_Kongzi_A_Historical_Large (5).pdf</data>
      <data key="created_at">1773740202</data>
    </node>
