    <node id="Kongzi Model Performance Metrics and RL Framework Documentation (image) [image_asset p5]">
      <data key="entity_type">image_asset</data>
      <data key="description">This image contains a page from a research paper detailing the performance improvements of the 'Kongzi' AI models (0.5B and 7B parameters) achieved through Reinforcement Learning (RL) training. It features a comprehensive data table comparing RL-trained models against SFT baselines across metrics like logical reasoning and problem solving when evaluated against GPT-4o, Gemini-2.5, and Qwen-Max. The text further elaborates on the GRPO reinforcement learning framework, defining specific reward functions for factual accuracy, formatting, and repetition penalties used to optimize the model's output.</data>
      <data key="source_id">image_asset:img-62760f22cb061980c29cae5907368eb4</data>
      <data key="is_image_node">1</data>
      <data key="img_path">C:\Users\lqx94\Documents\GitHub\doc\data\#00035\knowledge\multimodal\images\img-62760f22cb061980c29cae5907368eb4.png</data>
      <data key="file_path">3091_Kongzi_A_Historical_Large (5).pdf</data>
      <data key="page_idx">5</data>
      <data key="doc_id">doc-2e4bcd2653b550df61d289d0234df167</data>
      <data key="created_at">1773740214</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Kongzi Model Performance Evaluation and Conclusion Page (image) [image_asset p6]">
      <data key="entity_type">image_asset</data>
      <data key="description">This image captures page 7 of a research paper introducing 'Kongzi,' a language model designed for historical domains. It features Table 2, presenting benchmark results on CMMLU-Chinese-History comparing Kongzi against models like Qwen and Deepseek. The text details the evaluation methodology involving human and LLM scoring and concludes with a summary of the model's achievements through reinforcement learning and cold-start training, followed by a list of references.</data>
      <data key="source_id">image_asset:img-33dbc54f9e8644b13857c29090370274</data>
      <data key="is_image_node">1</data>
